00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:53.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:53.280 --> 00:10:55.430 align:middle line:84%
That was definitely part
of the problem, which

00:10:55.430 --> 00:10:58.100 align:middle line:84%
was there was a lot of
financial innovation

00:10:58.100 --> 00:10:59.970 align:middle line:90%
that had taken place.

00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:01.740 align:middle line:84%
Much like today,
where you have all

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:03.510 align:middle line:84%
the different
financial innovation

00:11:03.510 --> 00:11:04.840 align:middle line:90%
that's been taking place.

00:11:04.840 --> 00:11:07.260 align:middle line:84%
And then in addition,
there was also,

00:11:07.260 --> 00:11:11.130 align:middle line:84%
as is now or prior to our
current financial crises,

00:11:11.130 --> 00:11:15.150 align:middle line:84%
back then also there was this
level of irrational exuberance

00:11:15.150 --> 00:11:17.820 align:middle line:84%
on the part of
consumers, investors,

00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:20.710 align:middle line:84%
and that led to the
crash, essentially.

00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And so there was
legislation that

00:11:24.630 --> 00:11:27.850 align:middle line:84%
was put in place to reverse
some of the effects of that.

00:11:27.850 --> 00:11:30.510 align:middle line:10%
And so we continued
on for a few decades,

00:11:30.510 --> 00:11:34.050 align:middle line:10%
until about 1950, where this
legislation was followed.

00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:35.730 align:middle line:84%
And one of the key
legislations also

00:11:35.730 --> 00:11:42.000 align:middle line:84%
was that commercial banks had to
have a high deposit insurance.

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:44.760 align:middle line:84%
Meaning that their
level of trying

00:11:44.760 --> 00:11:46.770 align:middle line:84%
to get into very
risky areas would then

00:11:46.770 --> 00:11:49.410 align:middle line:90%
be minimized because of that.

00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:55.410 align:middle line:84%
But however, starting in
about late 1950s, early 1960s,

00:11:55.410 --> 00:11:57.300 align:middle line:84%
a number of things
happened that began

00:11:57.300 --> 00:11:59.520 align:middle line:84%
to reverse all the
safeguards that

00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:02.280 align:middle line:84%
had been put in place
from the previous crises.

00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at it then,
roughly in about-- in 1960s,

00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:07.440 align:middle line:90%
two things happened.

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:12.930 align:middle line:84%
First, we saw the
emergence of a market fund.

00:12:12.930 --> 00:12:16.710 align:middle line:10%
And why that's significant
is because all year round,

00:12:16.710 --> 00:12:20.010 align:middle line:10%
investments had
been taking place

00:12:20.010 --> 00:12:22.530 align:middle line:10%
because individuals were
investing their own money,

00:12:22.530 --> 00:12:25.140 align:middle line:10%
so there was a much higher
degree of due diligence.

00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:27.720 align:middle line:10%
There was a lot more
thinking about what's

00:12:27.720 --> 00:12:29.250 align:middle line:10%
the risk if I lose this money.

00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:32.390 align:middle line:10%
And so things were invested
where probably there

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:33.900 align:middle line:10%
were safe returns
and where there

00:12:33.900 --> 00:12:36.990 align:middle line:10%
was some useful
development taking place.

00:12:36.990 --> 00:12:39.840 align:middle line:10%
But then with the emergence
of this market fund,

00:12:39.840 --> 00:12:43.350 align:middle line:10%
it was now all these
investments from individuals

00:12:43.350 --> 00:12:46.800 align:middle line:10%
were pulled together
by a market manager.

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:50.140 align:middle line:10%
And so it was other people's
money that was at risk.

00:12:50.140 --> 00:12:53.970 align:middle line:10%
And so the fund manager didn't
have the same kind of skin

00:12:53.970 --> 00:12:55.620 align:middle line:10%
in the game, if you will.

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:58.350 align:middle line:10%
And plus, the way that the
market funds were incented

00:12:58.350 --> 00:13:03.330 align:middle line:10%
were completely driven
by going for volume

00:13:03.330 --> 00:13:06.540 align:middle line:10%
of assets that a
fund controlled,

00:13:06.540 --> 00:13:09.210 align:middle line:10%
rather than quality
of investments.

00:13:09.210 --> 00:13:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And so that was one big shift
that took place in the 1960s.

00:13:12.810 --> 00:13:14.850 align:middle line:84%
And then the second
thing was that there

00:13:14.850 --> 00:13:18.480 align:middle line:84%
was the emergence of
the money market funds

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:24.210 align:middle line:84%
as well, which made these
investment banks take away

00:13:24.210 --> 00:13:26.980 align:middle line:84%
some of the core activities
of commercial banks.

00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:29.010 align:middle line:10%
The commercial banks
had an incentive

00:13:29.010 --> 00:13:32.580 align:middle line:10%
to operate more safely,
but investment banks

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:35.070 align:middle line:10%
didn't have the same
kind of stipulations

00:13:35.070 --> 00:13:37.560 align:middle line:10%
as the commercial
banks, but now could

00:13:37.560 --> 00:13:40.380 align:middle line:10%
operate doing the same thing
that commercial banks are

00:13:40.380 --> 00:13:42.580 align:middle line:10%
doing in a much more risky way.

00:13:42.580 --> 00:13:45.300 align:middle line:10%
So you begin to see the
controls being taken away

00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:49.650 align:middle line:10%
and the sanity that existed
falling away quickly.

00:13:49.650 --> 00:13:52.650 align:middle line:84%
And then in the 1970s,
there was a huge shift.

00:13:52.650 --> 00:13:56.190 align:middle line:84%
Early 1970s, '71,
where we departed

00:13:56.190 --> 00:13:57.810 align:middle line:90%
from the gold standard.

00:13:57.810 --> 00:14:00.757 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of a
linchpin, if you will,

00:14:00.757 --> 00:14:01.590 align:middle line:90%
in this whole thing.

00:14:01.590 --> 00:14:04.600 align:middle line:84%
Because gold, if
we think about it,

00:14:04.600 --> 00:14:09.571 align:middle line:84%
it's a finite product that
you can see very clearly.

00:14:09.571 --> 00:14:11.070 align:middle line:84%
In all of history,
there is supposed

00:14:11.070 --> 00:14:15.930 align:middle line:84%
to have been only 20 cubic
meters that had been mined.

00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:19.470 align:middle line:84%
And the amount of
money that a nation,

00:14:19.470 --> 00:14:23.070 align:middle line:84%
that any individual nation
could put into the market

00:14:23.070 --> 00:14:25.710 align:middle line:84%
was related to the amount of
gold that they actually had.

00:14:25.710 --> 00:14:27.780 align:middle line:90%
So it is a very tight system.

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:29.910 align:middle line:84%
And so as a result of
being a tight system,

00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:33.960 align:middle line:84%
you couldn't have things like
runaway inflation occurring.

00:14:33.960 --> 00:14:37.770 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't have the money
supply going out of control.

00:14:37.770 --> 00:14:41.340 align:middle line:10%
But all that was taken away when
the gold standard was exited.

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:45.540 align:middle line:10%
And then also when the
gold standard was exited,

00:14:45.540 --> 00:14:49.560 align:middle line:10%
essentially, gold was
pegged to the US dollar.

00:14:49.560 --> 00:14:55.265 align:middle line:84%
So for example, one ounce of
gold was worth $35 at the time.

00:14:55.265 --> 00:14:56.065 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:14:56.065 --> 00:14:59.050 align:middle line:90%
And today, and $1,700 roughly.

00:14:59.050 --> 00:14:59.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:59.850 --> 00:15:01.670 align:middle line:90%
It's completely out of control.

00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:05.670 align:middle line:84%
But essentially what
happened then was that all

00:15:05.670 --> 00:15:08.130 align:middle line:84%
the different-- when the gold
standard was exited, then

00:15:08.130 --> 00:15:10.680 align:middle line:84%
all the reserves of dollars
that different countries

00:15:10.680 --> 00:15:13.710 align:middle line:84%
around the world had
lost their value.

00:15:13.710 --> 00:15:16.440 align:middle line:90%
Because the gold began to rise--

00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:19.410 align:middle line:84%
the value of gold went
up from $35 to a lot more

00:15:19.410 --> 00:15:21.870 align:middle line:90%
when you exited the standard.

00:15:21.870 --> 00:15:27.030 align:middle line:84%
And in effect, another big
shift that happened at that time

00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:28.200 align:middle line:90%
was the oil--

00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:29.000 align:middle line:90%
OPEC.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:32.610 align:middle line:10%
The Oil Petroleum
Exporting Community.

00:15:32.610 --> 00:15:39.752 align:middle line:10%
They realized that they needed
to shift away from this--

00:15:39.752 --> 00:15:41.460 align:middle line:10%
they needed to create
a new standard now.

00:15:41.460 --> 00:15:46.700 align:middle line:84%
So they hiked up the price
of oil substantially.

00:15:46.700 --> 00:15:47.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Which was the new gold.

00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:48.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Which was the new gold.

00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:49.440 align:middle line:90%
Yes, exactly.

00:15:49.440 --> 00:15:49.700 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:15:49.700 --> 00:15:49.770 align:middle line:90%


00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:50.610 align:middle line:90%
>> The Petrodollar.

00:15:50.610 --> 00:15:51.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:54.900 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened,
that began to then

00:15:54.900 --> 00:15:56.400 align:middle line:84%
have its repercussions
in that there

00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:59.450 align:middle line:84%
was a lot of inflation
that created in the US

00:15:59.450 --> 00:16:03.560 align:middle line:84%
and globally because
of the divergence

00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:09.350 align:middle line:84%
of different global
currencies from the dollar.

00:16:09.350 --> 00:16:12.400 align:middle line:84%
You begin to have
a lot of variation

00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:16.910 align:middle line:84%
in the way that
money that was drawn

00:16:16.910 --> 00:16:19.390 align:middle line:90%
at the level of each country.

00:16:19.390 --> 00:16:22.640 align:middle line:84%
There was inflation that began
to occur all over the world.

00:16:22.640 --> 00:16:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think those
few shifts meant

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:30.290 align:middle line:84%
that 1973, 1974, because
of the uncertainty, we

00:16:30.290 --> 00:16:38.540 align:middle line:84%
entered into a huge bear market,
the 1973-74 bear market, which

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:41.150 align:middle line:84%
it occurs because
of this shift away

00:16:41.150 --> 00:16:42.960 align:middle line:84%
from the gold standard
to the oil standard.

00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:48.350 align:middle line:84%
>> And so at this time, we're in
the markets where John or Jane

00:16:48.350 --> 00:16:55.400 align:middle line:84%
Doe would say, I want to invest
in, say, an auto manufacturer.

00:16:55.400 --> 00:16:56.680 align:middle line:90%
One of the blue chip stocks.

00:16:56.680 --> 00:16:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Something where
you knew that cars

00:16:58.430 --> 00:17:00.410 align:middle line:84%
were going to be in
demand at a certain rate.

00:17:00.410 --> 00:17:02.360 align:middle line:90%
It was a safe investment.

00:17:02.360 --> 00:17:04.430 align:middle line:84%
It was an intelligent,
logical investment

00:17:04.430 --> 00:17:05.540 align:middle line:90%
from their perspective.

00:17:05.540 --> 00:17:08.940 align:middle line:84%
They studied it and looked
at the profits and losses.

00:17:08.940 --> 00:17:11.420 align:middle line:84%
So now that goes with the
money market funds come in.

00:17:11.420 --> 00:17:13.490 align:middle line:84%
When we detach from
gold, then, we're

00:17:13.490 --> 00:17:18.410 align:middle line:84%
going into the instability
of an oil-based environment

00:17:18.410 --> 00:17:20.225 align:middle line:84%
economically, which
then is bringing,

00:17:20.225 --> 00:17:23.625 align:middle line:84%
now, all of these weird
political instabilities, right?

00:17:23.625 --> 00:17:24.425 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, absolutely.

00:17:24.425 --> 00:17:25.225 align:middle line:90%
>> Globally.

00:17:25.225 --> 00:17:27.500 align:middle line:84%
So that brings even
more instability in.

00:17:27.500 --> 00:17:30.060 align:middle line:84%
Inflation takes hold
all around the world.

00:17:30.060 --> 00:17:30.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:30.860 --> 00:17:34.400 align:middle line:84%
>> And now we're setting the
stage for what happens then

00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:36.650 align:middle line:90%
in the 1980s.

00:17:36.650 --> 00:17:37.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:37.610 --> 00:17:40.640 align:middle line:84%
So the manifest sign that
things have really shifted

00:17:40.640 --> 00:17:42.382 align:middle line:90%
occurs in 1987.

00:17:42.382 --> 00:17:44.840 align:middle line:84%
But there's, again, a few shifts
that happened before that.

00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:47.270 align:middle line:10%
So the manifest
sign, in 1987, you

00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:49.770 align:middle line:10%
have a synchronized
global crash.

00:17:49.770 --> 00:17:53.120 align:middle line:10%
And this is the first time that
stock markets around the world

00:17:53.120 --> 00:17:58.190 align:middle line:10%
drop in tremendous value in
a short time simultaneously.

00:17:58.190 --> 00:18:00.410 align:middle line:84%
And that means that
the notion of value

00:18:00.410 --> 00:18:01.850 align:middle line:90%
has completely shifted now.

00:18:01.850 --> 00:18:05.300 align:middle line:10%
Because earlier,
whereas say, investing

00:18:05.300 --> 00:18:08.300 align:middle line:10%
in a country like Brazil
or India or the US

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:13.940 align:middle line:10%
meant something different, in
that your development in the US

00:18:13.940 --> 00:18:17.961 align:middle line:10%
was completely different
from development in, say,

00:18:17.961 --> 00:18:19.835 align:middle line:10%
a developing country
like India [INAUDIBLE]..

00:18:19.835 --> 00:18:20.635 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:18:20.635 --> 00:18:22.560 align:middle line:84%
The emerging markets
started coming into play.

00:18:22.560 --> 00:18:24.770 align:middle line:84%
Which aren't those just
ripe for political and other

00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:25.649 align:middle line:90%
exploitation?

00:18:25.649 --> 00:18:27.065 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to be
totally manipulated?

00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:27.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:18:27.710 --> 00:18:28.640 align:middle line:90%
Yes, absolutely.

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And there's-- I know you've met
and interviewed John Perkins.

00:18:33.630 --> 00:18:34.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes,

00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:38.720 align:middle line:84%
>> And his book, "Confessions
of an Economic Hit Man"

00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:40.430 align:middle line:90%
really cover that very well.

00:18:40.430 --> 00:18:44.750 align:middle line:10%
But then in addition to that,
what begins to happen in 1982,

00:18:44.750 --> 00:18:49.010 align:middle line:10%
you see the emergence of the
emerging market fund, which

00:18:49.010 --> 00:18:52.190 align:middle line:10%
means that not only
are, in a certain sense,

00:18:52.190 --> 00:18:54.890 align:middle line:10%
countries becoming part
of this, quote unquote,

00:18:54.890 --> 00:19:00.440 align:middle line:10%
"secret" empire of,
say, United States,

00:19:00.440 --> 00:19:03.020 align:middle line:10%
but now what's happening is
because of the emerging market

00:19:03.020 --> 00:19:06.710 align:middle line:10%
fund, you have a
large number of--

00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:09.260 align:middle line:10%
you have a lot
more money that can

00:19:09.260 --> 00:19:15.710 align:middle line:10%
be handled by any company in the
emerging markets suddenly being

00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:18.950 align:middle line:10%
thrust upon those emerging
markets at the corporate level.

00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:23.760 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's always tied to their
raw resources at some level.

00:19:23.760 --> 00:19:24.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:24.890 --> 00:19:25.800 align:middle line:90%
Yes, absolutely.

00:19:25.800 --> 00:19:28.091 align:middle line:84%
>> And there are some moral,
ethical issues we could go

00:19:28.091 --> 00:19:30.140 align:middle line:84%
into at length
just on that alone.

00:19:30.140 --> 00:19:31.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

00:19:31.340 --> 00:19:32.340 align:middle line:90%
Yes, absolutely.

00:19:32.340 --> 00:19:39.920 align:middle line:84%
Because the fact is that the
way that this money comes in,

00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:45.140 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of inflation that
takes place in that country.

00:19:45.140 --> 00:19:48.360 align:middle line:84%
And then very often,
the corporations who are

00:19:48.360 --> 00:19:52.650 align:middle line:84%
a recipient of the funds cannot
make payments, and so on.

00:19:52.650 --> 00:19:56.489 align:middle line:84%
And then there's a
lot of, as you say,

00:19:56.489 --> 00:19:58.530 align:middle line:84%
there's moral and ethical
issues in terms of what

00:19:58.530 --> 00:19:59.950 align:middle line:90%
they need to do to pay it back.

00:19:59.950 --> 00:20:02.241 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, and whether or not
the people even have access

00:20:02.241 --> 00:20:05.000 align:middle line:84%
to their own resources
anymore oftentimes, right?

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:09.590 align:middle line:84%
Because those are now held
in global corporate hands.

00:20:09.590 --> 00:20:12.020 align:middle line:84%
So OK, so now we've got
the emerging markets

00:20:12.020 --> 00:20:14.900 align:middle line:84%
coming in and destabilizing
the emerging economies

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:16.550 align:middle line:84%
of the world,
after we've already

00:20:16.550 --> 00:20:21.300 align:middle line:84%
destabilized all of the
first-world economies,

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:22.700 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:20:22.700 --> 00:20:23.630 align:middle line:90%
So then what happens?

00:20:23.630 --> 00:20:26.737 align:middle line:90%
We go into the 1990s, and then--

00:20:26.737 --> 00:20:28.070 align:middle line:90%
well, we've got junk bonds and--

00:20:28.070 --> 00:20:28.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Junk bonds.

00:20:28.450 --> 00:20:29.130 align:middle line:90%
>> --Michael Milken.

00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:29.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:29.930 --> 00:20:34.620 align:middle line:84%
In 1984, you have
two things happening.

00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:40.070 align:middle line:10%
One is that you've got the
mortgage-backed bonds that have

00:20:40.070 --> 00:20:44.520 align:middle line:10%
now been legitimized,
and that's a very--

00:20:44.520 --> 00:20:47.810 align:middle line:10%
again, a very tricky
issue, and the center

00:20:47.810 --> 00:20:52.040 align:middle line:10%
of a lot of toxic assets
that have been responsible

00:20:52.040 --> 00:20:54.810 align:middle line:10%
for even today, the
global financial crises.

00:20:54.810 --> 00:20:59.380 align:middle line:10%
So one can see that that
mainstream, toxic asset

00:20:59.380 --> 00:21:01.120 align:middle line:10%
mentality was started
at that point,

00:21:01.120 --> 00:21:04.840 align:middle line:10%
around 1984, when
mortgage-backed bonds were

00:21:04.840 --> 00:21:06.220 align:middle line:10%
legitimized.

00:21:06.220 --> 00:21:10.870 align:middle line:10%
And again, the psychology
is that you're moving away

00:21:10.870 --> 00:21:14.200 align:middle line:10%
from that safe investment
that a bank makes

00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:17.230 align:middle line:10%
to an individual
homeowner, and here you're

00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:20.280 align:middle line:10%
beginning to set the
stage for pooling together

00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:23.410 align:middle line:10%
a bunch of mortgages
into special purpose

00:21:23.410 --> 00:21:25.990 align:middle line:10%
vehicles that
investment banks set up,

00:21:25.990 --> 00:21:27.910 align:middle line:10%
and then that becomes
the basis for all kinds

00:21:27.910 --> 00:21:30.430 align:middle line:10%
of other financial
products that really

00:21:30.430 --> 00:21:33.130 align:middle line:10%
have no basis in reality.

00:21:33.130 --> 00:21:35.340 align:middle line:90%
>> And then foreign exchange.

00:21:35.340 --> 00:21:37.510 align:middle line:84%
