00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:22.870 align:middle line:84%
So oil is a great metaphor
for this vital consciousness.

00:31:22.870 --> 00:31:24.810 align:middle line:84%
And the question
is, what's next?

00:31:24.810 --> 00:31:27.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, and it brings with
it also that aggression

00:31:27.700 --> 00:31:30.435 align:middle line:84%
and potential chaos and
instability of that phase

00:31:30.435 --> 00:31:31.235 align:middle line:90%
of growth.

00:31:31.235 --> 00:31:32.035 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:31:32.035 --> 00:31:32.980 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:31:32.980 --> 00:31:34.030 align:middle line:90%
>> And so next?

00:31:34.030 --> 00:31:39.670 align:middle line:84%
>> And so what's next,
that's this notion of another

00:31:39.670 --> 00:31:40.470 align:middle line:90%
standard.

00:31:40.470 --> 00:31:42.700 align:middle line:84%
And in the book,
what I talk about,

00:31:42.700 --> 00:31:47.410 align:middle line:84%
potentially, is perhaps
a solar standard, but--

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:48.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Solar.

00:31:48.210 --> 00:31:49.440 align:middle line:90%
>> A solar standard.

00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:54.160 align:middle line:84%
But the real-- the point
being is that this is not--

00:31:54.160 --> 00:31:58.150 align:middle line:84%
solar energy is
existing everywhere.

00:31:58.150 --> 00:32:01.231 align:middle line:84%
It's not something that
you capture and put,

00:32:01.231 --> 00:32:02.105 align:middle line:90%
and that you control.

00:32:02.105 --> 00:32:02.938 align:middle line:90%
>> You can't own it.

00:32:02.938 --> 00:32:06.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's available
to everybody.

00:32:06.170 --> 00:32:11.300 align:middle line:84%
It exists in the different
kinds of services

00:32:11.300 --> 00:32:13.510 align:middle line:90%
that nature provides around us.

00:32:13.510 --> 00:32:16.750 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they all have solar
energy embedded in them.

00:32:16.750 --> 00:32:19.060 align:middle line:84%
Even if we think
about plants, they've

00:32:19.060 --> 00:32:22.060 align:middle line:84%
come into being because of
the way that they've converted

00:32:22.060 --> 00:32:24.910 align:middle line:90%
solar energy to something else.

00:32:24.910 --> 00:32:28.360 align:middle line:84%
And so here what we're saying
is that there is essentially

00:32:28.360 --> 00:32:29.889 align:middle line:90%
a kind of a--

00:32:29.889 --> 00:32:31.430 align:middle line:84%
if we think about
it in market terms,

00:32:31.430 --> 00:32:34.570 align:middle line:84%
there needs to be a
democratization of markets.

00:32:34.570 --> 00:32:38.370 align:middle line:84%
And that solar standard is the
metaphor for that, if you will.

00:32:38.370 --> 00:32:41.150 align:middle line:84%
>> And something that links
back to something of true value.

00:32:41.150 --> 00:32:41.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Of true value.

00:32:41.950 --> 00:32:42.750 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:42.750 --> 00:32:44.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Where the assets
of true value,

00:32:44.200 --> 00:32:46.180 align:middle line:84%
resources or whatever
of true value.

00:32:46.180 --> 00:32:48.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

00:32:48.070 --> 00:32:51.680 align:middle line:84%
>> And so we're a
long way from there.

00:32:51.680 --> 00:32:52.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:32:52.910 --> 00:32:54.770 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:54.770 --> 00:32:58.610 align:middle line:84%
Now, I think that there
are a couple of things.

00:32:58.610 --> 00:33:05.750 align:middle line:84%
One is that so if we analyze
where we're at right now,

00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:09.170 align:middle line:84%
we're very much-- if we--
just by looking at the volume

00:33:09.170 --> 00:33:11.900 align:middle line:84%
activity, the reach
of activity, we

00:33:11.900 --> 00:33:13.570 align:middle line:84%
can see we're at
the vital level.

00:33:13.570 --> 00:33:17.330 align:middle line:84%
But even looking at it
much more specifically,

00:33:17.330 --> 00:33:20.410 align:middle line:84%
the number of stock market
indices that have been created.

00:33:20.410 --> 00:33:25.700 align:middle line:84%
You had cited the 55
trillion to 120 trillion

00:33:25.700 --> 00:33:27.100 align:middle line:90%
in just less than a decade.

00:33:27.100 --> 00:33:27.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Six years.

00:33:27.900 --> 00:33:28.740 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:31.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Just the number of
crashes that have occurred.

00:33:31.670 --> 00:33:34.160 align:middle line:90%
The variation in stock price.

00:33:34.160 --> 00:33:37.940 align:middle line:84%
The daily gains and
losses that have--

00:33:37.940 --> 00:33:39.290 align:middle line:90%
the variation in that itself.

00:33:39.290 --> 00:33:41.330 align:middle line:90%
That's all part of the vital--

00:33:41.330 --> 00:33:43.950 align:middle line:84%
the fact that that's happening
so much more in the last 10,

00:33:43.950 --> 00:33:47.690 align:middle line:84%
15 years is a sure indication
that the stock market

00:33:47.690 --> 00:33:50.340 align:middle line:90%
itself is at the vital level.

00:33:50.340 --> 00:33:56.470 align:middle line:84%
And if we go back to this
notion of what's next,

00:33:56.470 --> 00:34:00.740 align:middle line:84%
what I'm proposing is that
this physical to the vital

00:34:00.740 --> 00:34:04.420 align:middle line:84%
to the mental, so this
seed becoming a flower

00:34:04.420 --> 00:34:10.370 align:middle line:84%
is a sustainable
pattern of progress.

00:34:10.370 --> 00:34:12.650 align:middle line:84%
And so we see it in
the flower, but even

00:34:12.650 --> 00:34:17.420 align:middle line:84%
if we think about many different
progressive developments that

00:34:17.420 --> 00:34:21.050 align:middle line:84%
have taken place
across the earth,

00:34:21.050 --> 00:34:22.739 align:middle line:84%
we'll see that
same pattern, where

00:34:22.739 --> 00:34:24.889 align:middle line:84%
there's a shift from the
physical to the vital

00:34:24.889 --> 00:34:26.719 align:middle line:90%
to the mental.

00:34:26.719 --> 00:34:29.000 align:middle line:84%
And so when we
think about what's

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:32.449 align:middle line:84%
next in terms of the
market, then there

00:34:32.449 --> 00:34:36.590 align:middle line:84%
is this notion that we
have to move from the vital

00:34:36.590 --> 00:34:38.199 align:middle line:90%
to the mental.

00:34:38.199 --> 00:34:42.330 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think you've made
a really good case for that.

00:34:42.330 --> 00:34:46.850 align:middle line:84%
We can't stay in this unstable
phase any longer, that's

00:34:46.850 --> 00:34:50.989 align:middle line:84%
essentially ready to burst
beyond anything physical

00:34:50.989 --> 00:34:52.949 align:middle line:90%
or tangible any longer.

00:34:52.949 --> 00:34:54.920 align:middle line:84%
And so when we're
in this vital stage,

00:34:54.920 --> 00:34:58.820 align:middle line:84%
at the same time, as
you have mentioned,

00:34:58.820 --> 00:35:02.420 align:middle line:84%
we have moved into, essentially,
a global community when

00:35:02.420 --> 00:35:04.190 align:middle line:90%
it comes to commerce and money.

00:35:04.190 --> 00:35:06.230 align:middle line:90%
Globalization has occurred.

00:35:06.230 --> 00:35:08.240 align:middle line:84%
This isn't a concept
in the future.

00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:11.330 align:middle line:90%


00:35:11.330 --> 00:35:19.970 align:middle line:84%
So how do you bring the mental
aspect of commerce and movement

00:35:19.970 --> 00:35:23.540 align:middle line:84%
of funds and such-- not funds,
but development of markets,

00:35:23.540 --> 00:35:26.540 align:middle line:84%
into this globalization,
this global environment that

00:35:26.540 --> 00:35:29.600 align:middle line:84%
has already occurred,
in a democratic fashion,

00:35:29.600 --> 00:35:32.840 align:middle line:84%
as an example of the
solar or the sun influence

00:35:32.840 --> 00:35:34.490 align:middle line:90%
on the planet and the seed?

00:35:34.490 --> 00:35:36.060 align:middle line:90%
How does that-- how do we begin?

00:35:36.060 --> 00:35:36.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:35:36.860 --> 00:35:39.620 align:middle line:84%
I think that's really
the crux of it.

00:35:39.620 --> 00:35:42.290 align:middle line:84%
But I just want to say
one more thing, actually.

00:35:42.290 --> 00:35:47.780 align:middle line:10%
And that's when we think
about the vital level,

00:35:47.780 --> 00:35:51.020 align:middle line:10%
it's like this.

00:35:51.020 --> 00:35:52.730 align:middle line:10%
We've talked about
the volume of flows

00:35:52.730 --> 00:35:55.250 align:middle line:10%
that have changed, the rhythm
of flows that have changed

00:35:55.250 --> 00:36:00.980 align:middle line:10%
substantially, and
essentially, the recipient

00:36:00.980 --> 00:36:04.850 align:middle line:10%
of any of these volume
and rhythm of flows

00:36:04.850 --> 00:36:07.400 align:middle line:10%
now gets subjected
at the vital level

00:36:07.400 --> 00:36:08.840 align:middle line:10%
to something
completely different

00:36:08.840 --> 00:36:11.810 align:middle line:10%
from their innate nature.

00:36:11.810 --> 00:36:14.990 align:middle line:84%
And so what's happening
is that if there

00:36:14.990 --> 00:36:19.490 align:middle line:84%
is any kind of resonance in
that receiving object or market

00:36:19.490 --> 00:36:23.090 align:middle line:84%
or corporation to
these forces, then--

00:36:23.090 --> 00:36:25.700 align:middle line:84%
which we know are
totally vital--

00:36:25.700 --> 00:36:30.120 align:middle line:84%
then that aspect comes
forward from that entity.

00:36:30.120 --> 00:36:34.760 align:middle line:84%
So what we've seen today in the
play out of the vital market

00:36:34.760 --> 00:36:39.500 align:middle line:84%
is essentially the
vital part of what's

00:36:39.500 --> 00:36:43.250 align:middle line:84%
contained in markets
or in corporations

00:36:43.250 --> 00:36:47.390 align:middle line:84%
or in people is what's
coming to the front.

00:36:47.390 --> 00:36:49.105 align:middle line:90%
And so there's a resonance.

00:36:49.105 --> 00:36:50.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Give us an example of that.

00:36:50.790 --> 00:36:53.900 align:middle line:90%
So I know exactly what you mean.

00:36:53.900 --> 00:36:57.430 align:middle line:90%
>> So just stepping back in--

00:36:57.430 --> 00:36:58.363 align:middle line:90%
two things.

00:36:58.363 --> 00:36:59.700 align:middle line:90%
I'll talk about two things.

00:36:59.700 --> 00:37:07.770 align:middle line:84%
One is that the notion of
when something is subjected

00:37:07.770 --> 00:37:11.979 align:middle line:84%
to love, for instance,
then if there's love in it,

00:37:11.979 --> 00:37:13.145 align:middle line:90%
it's going to respond with--

00:37:13.145 --> 00:37:17.720 align:middle line:84%
then love is going to
probably come forward.

00:37:17.720 --> 00:37:22.420 align:middle line:84%
If something is subjected to
hate, if there's hate in it,

00:37:22.420 --> 00:37:24.780 align:middle line:90%
hate is going to come forward.

00:37:24.780 --> 00:37:29.990 align:middle line:84%
So these incredible vital flows,
which are about fear and greed,

00:37:29.990 --> 00:37:35.450 align:middle line:84%
they're creating a resonance at
a very minute or micro level,

00:37:35.450 --> 00:37:41.120 align:middle line:84%
at the individual level, at
the level of corporations,

00:37:41.120 --> 00:37:43.760 align:middle line:84%
to also function
in a similar way.

00:37:43.760 --> 00:37:49.670 align:middle line:84%
So the very fact that we've gone
through this huge arc whereby

00:37:49.670 --> 00:37:52.070 align:middle line:84%
everything has been
appropriated into, in a sense,

00:37:52.070 --> 00:37:59.060 align:middle line:84%
one global mechanism means that
all these different entities,

00:37:59.060 --> 00:38:02.690 align:middle line:84%
there's a part of themselves,
or their consciousness

00:38:02.690 --> 00:38:07.320 align:middle line:84%
is being overshadowed by this
vital aspect of greed and fear,

00:38:07.320 --> 00:38:09.800 align:middle line:84%
and that's what we're
seeing a lot more of.

00:38:09.800 --> 00:38:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And so the question
is how do we bridge

00:38:11.780 --> 00:38:14.660 align:middle line:90%
from that to the mental level?

00:38:14.660 --> 00:38:16.406 align:middle line:90%
>> How do we?

00:38:16.406 --> 00:38:17.206 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:38:17.206 --> 00:38:18.580 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS] That's a question.

00:38:18.580 --> 00:38:19.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:21.680 align:middle line:90%
So there's a couple of things.

00:38:21.680 --> 00:38:29.500 align:middle line:10%
And I'd say that
practically speaking,

00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:34.870 align:middle line:10%
it can't be done suddenly,
because if it's--

00:38:34.870 --> 00:38:37.060 align:middle line:10%
all of a sudden, if we allowed--

00:38:37.060 --> 00:38:39.990 align:middle line:10%
if central banks
didn't intervene

00:38:39.990 --> 00:38:42.910 align:middle line:10%
in the way that they did
right now, in the last three

00:38:42.910 --> 00:38:45.520 align:middle line:10%
to four years, five years,
if they didn't suck up

00:38:45.520 --> 00:38:48.880 align:middle line:10%
junk assets, if they didn't
make sure the money supply was

00:38:48.880 --> 00:38:52.590 align:middle line:10%
unaffected, if they didn't
reduce interest rates, reduce--

00:38:52.590 --> 00:38:56.410 align:middle line:10%
relatively speaking-- tax
rates, then there would be--

00:38:56.410 --> 00:39:00.370 align:middle line:10%
because of the huge
fall off of a lot

00:39:00.370 --> 00:39:02.890 align:middle line:10%
of financial institutions,
there would be a huge crisis

00:39:02.890 --> 00:39:04.120 align:middle line:10%
that would occur overnight.

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:04.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:39:04.920 --> 00:39:05.420 align:middle line:90%
Globally.

00:39:05.420 --> 00:39:06.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Globally.

00:39:06.220 --> 00:39:07.360 align:middle line:90%
Globally yes.

00:39:07.360 --> 00:39:11.740 align:middle line:10%
And so if we think about
the intervention that's

00:39:11.740 --> 00:39:15.820 align:middle line:10%
happened from the central
banks, in a sense,

00:39:15.820 --> 00:39:20.290 align:middle line:10%
it's a good thing
because it's allowed

00:39:20.290 --> 00:39:22.840 align:middle line:10%
the way that people have
lived at the ground level

00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:24.130 align:middle line:10%
to continue.

00:39:24.130 --> 00:39:25.690 align:middle line:84%
The shock would
have been too great

00:39:25.690 --> 00:39:29.650 align:middle line:84%
if all these domineering
institutions were

00:39:29.650 --> 00:39:31.370 align:middle line:90%
allowed to fail overnight.

00:39:31.370 --> 00:39:33.700 align:middle line:84%
And I think that as we
talk about a transition

00:39:33.700 --> 00:39:35.914 align:middle line:84%
from vital to mental,
the very first step--

00:39:35.914 --> 00:39:37.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's
two ways to do it.

00:39:37.330 --> 00:39:39.880 align:middle line:10%
Either you can
stabilize a vital,

00:39:39.880 --> 00:39:41.380 align:middle line:10%
knowing that it's
very temporary,

00:39:41.380 --> 00:39:44.650 align:middle line:10%
and that now you need to build
a bridge towards the mental,

00:39:44.650 --> 00:39:47.440 align:middle line:10%
or you can just take a
leap into the mental,

00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:51.310 align:middle line:10%
and allow things to
totally crash and burn,

00:39:51.310 --> 00:39:54.100 align:middle line:10%
and then something else
will emerge from that,

00:39:54.100 --> 00:39:55.870 align:middle line:10%
but there'll be a lot
of pain associated

00:39:55.870 --> 00:39:58.220 align:middle line:10%
with it in the short term.

00:39:58.220 --> 00:40:01.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I think we're
at this critical stage

00:40:01.990 --> 00:40:05.170 align:middle line:84%
now where all these different
institutions continue

00:40:05.170 --> 00:40:07.060 align:middle line:90%
to uphold the--

00:40:07.060 --> 00:40:09.250 align:middle line:84%
>> The triage has
already occurred, right?

00:40:09.250 --> 00:40:13.930 align:middle line:84%
To keep people so they can
afford, for the most part, food

00:40:13.930 --> 00:40:16.510 align:middle line:84%
and a roof over
their heads, and--

00:40:16.510 --> 00:40:19.690 align:middle line:84%
the basics have continued
on for the most part.

00:40:19.690 --> 00:40:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And I know there are some
countries and people who

00:40:22.420 --> 00:40:25.960 align:middle line:90%
have suffered greatly.

00:40:25.960 --> 00:40:27.700 align:middle line:84%
But generally
speaking, globally,

00:40:27.700 --> 00:40:32.340 align:middle line:84%
life has gone on as usual, if
to a lower standard of living.

00:40:32.340 --> 00:40:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And that's true, and
it's brought up a lot

00:40:34.090 --> 00:40:37.000 align:middle line:90%
of questions for us to look at.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:38.510 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as the
money has gone away,

00:40:38.510 --> 00:40:40.510 align:middle line:90%
the ability for people to--

00:40:40.510 --> 00:40:43.030 align:middle line:84%
for example-- buy
homes has gone away.

00:40:43.030 --> 00:40:46.660 align:middle line:84%
Young people to be able to
have their own apartment.

00:40:46.660 --> 00:40:48.520 align:middle line:84%
A lot of that's gone
in the Western world.

00:40:48.520 --> 00:40:50.620 align:middle line:84%
Now people are living
together again.

00:40:50.620 --> 00:40:52.660 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people in
their 20s and even 30s

00:40:52.660 --> 00:40:55.240 align:middle line:84%
are moving back into their
parents' homes because

00:40:55.240 --> 00:40:57.070 align:middle line:84%
of the lack of
availability of work.

00:40:57.070 --> 00:41:00.220 align:middle line:84%
So this is part of
that triage period

00:41:00.220 --> 00:41:03.760 align:middle line:84%
where we're having to start
adjusting our view of what

00:41:03.760 --> 00:41:07.030 align:middle line:84%
has value in life,
which seems to me is

00:41:07.030 --> 00:41:10.810 align:middle line:84%
an appropriate precursor to
the mental, because isn't it

00:41:10.810 --> 00:41:14.060 align:middle line:84%
about establishing true
value again across the board?

00:41:14.060 --> 00:41:14.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

00:41:14.860 --> 00:41:15.660 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:41:15.660 --> 00:41:20.380 align:middle line:84%
And I think that from
the perspective of what

00:41:20.380 --> 00:41:25.300 align:middle line:84%
can be done at the level
of markets, so there's

00:41:25.300 --> 00:41:26.830 align:middle line:84%
this bridge that
needs to be built.

00:41:26.830 --> 00:41:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And the way that the
stock market itself

00:41:30.160 --> 00:41:35.620 align:middle line:84%
functions can be
altered to allow

00:41:35.620 --> 00:41:40.420 align:middle line:84%
more of a semblance of the
mental to come into being.

00:41:40.420 --> 00:41:51.880 align:middle line:84%
And essentially, one of the
leading models, if you will,

00:41:51.880 --> 00:41:54.520 align:middle line:84%
of modern financial development
has been this notion

00:41:54.520 --> 00:41:56.770 align:middle line:90%
of efficient market hypothesis.

00:41:56.770 --> 00:41:57.920 align:middle line:90%
>> And what does that mean?

00:41:57.920 --> 00:42:02.527 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's really where
a price, say, of a stock is,

00:42:02.527 --> 00:42:04.360 align:middle line:84%
quote, unquote,
"informationally efficient."

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:06.340 align:middle line:84%
It means it captures
all the realities that's

00:42:06.340 --> 00:42:07.755 align:middle line:90%
happening in the market.

00:42:07.755 --> 00:42:10.900 align:middle line:84%
And so the price
totally reflects

00:42:10.900 --> 00:42:14.650 align:middle line:84%
all the issues that need
to be considered and--

00:42:14.650 --> 00:42:18.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Of the health of that
particular entity or company

00:42:18.200 --> 00:42:19.000 align:middle line:90%
or whatnot.

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:19.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

00:42:19.820 --> 00:42:21.755 align:middle line:90%
I mean, so in efficient market--

00:42:21.755 --> 00:42:23.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Going back to the
way it used to be.

00:42:23.380 --> 00:42:25.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Going back to the
way it used to be, yes.

00:42:25.330 --> 00:42:29.500 align:middle line:84%
In efficient market
hypothesis, prices never lie.

00:42:29.500 --> 00:42:33.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's all
about reflecting

00:42:33.280 --> 00:42:34.890 align:middle line:90%
exactly what the reality is.

00:42:34.890 --> 00:42:39.719 align:middle line:10%
But we know for a fact
that financial markets

00:42:39.719 --> 00:42:41.260 align:middle line:10%
don't function that
way, because they

00:42:41.260 --> 00:42:45.160 align:middle line:10%
function by this notion
of greed and fear.

00:42:45.160 --> 00:42:48.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Does this mean establishing
a new type of index based

00:42:48.370 --> 00:42:50.150 align:middle line:90%
on that, for example?

00:42:50.150 --> 00:42:50.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:42:50.950 --> 00:42:51.750 align:middle line:90%
Yes, definitely.

00:42:51.750 --> 00:42:54.950 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a few different
things that need to be done.

00:42:54.950 --> 00:42:58.300 align:middle line:84%
But I brought that up because
what I was trying to get at

00:42:58.300 --> 00:43:01.630 align:middle line:84%
was that the way that the
stock is traded right now

00:43:01.630 --> 00:43:03.970 align:middle line:84%
is not based on efficient
market hypothesis,

00:43:03.970 --> 00:43:07.420 align:middle line:84%
it's based on this
notion of fear and greed.

00:43:07.420 --> 00:43:10.930 align:middle line:10%
And if we want to begin to
approach the mental level,

00:43:10.930 --> 00:43:12.670 align:middle line:10%
we have to change
the way that stock

00:43:12.670 --> 00:43:18.174 align:middle line:10%
is created so that it
approaches more this reality

00:43:18.174 --> 00:43:19.465 align:middle line:10%
of efficient market hypothesis.

00:43:19.465 --> 00:43:22.240 align:middle line:10%
So When we think about
efficient market hypothesis,

00:43:22.240 --> 00:43:24.100 align:middle line:10%
it's having a lot
more information

00:43:24.100 --> 00:43:26.830 align:middle line:10%
that's true about the
environment being reflected

00:43:26.830 --> 00:43:27.670 align:middle line:10%
in the stock price.

00:43:27.670 --> 00:43:28.300 align:middle line:10%
>> Transparency, too.

00:43:28.300 --> 00:43:29.110 align:middle line:10%
>> Transparency.

00:43:29.110 --> 00:43:29.910 align:middle line:10%
Yes, absolutely.

00:43:29.910 --> 00:43:33.520 align:middle line:10%
And so all the costs
that were externalized,

00:43:33.520 --> 00:43:35.900 align:middle line:10%
whether environmentally,
socially,

00:43:35.900 --> 00:43:38.650 align:middle line:10%
that were not reflected
in the price of an asset

00:43:38.650 --> 00:43:40.960 align:middle line:10%
or the price of a stock
need to be reflected

00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:42.580 align:middle line:10%
in the price of the stock.

00:43:42.580 --> 00:43:45.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's not going
to be done voluntarily.

00:43:45.350 --> 00:43:48.490 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to be done by the
way these indexes are set up.

00:43:48.490 --> 00:43:52.840 align:middle line:84%
So we would have to, in
a sense, change the way

00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:56.200 align:middle line:84%
the stock market functions so
that that information can come

00:43:56.200 --> 00:44:02.140 align:middle line:84%
into it that's required so
that the right kind of trades

00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:05.000 align:middle line:84%
happen based on the true cost
or the true price of what's

00:44:05.000 --> 00:44:05.800 align:middle line:90%
being traded.

00:44:05.800 --> 00:44:05.904 align:middle line:90%
>> Mhm.

00:44:05.904 --> 00:44:07.030 align:middle line:90%
It makes total sense.

00:44:07.030 --> 00:44:07.420 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:44:07.420 --> 00:44:09.620 align:middle line:84%
>> And then the point that
you had brought up around

00:44:09.620 --> 00:44:10.670 align:middle line:90%
the index.

00:44:10.670 --> 00:44:13.720 align:middle line:84%
Yes, a totally new kind of
index needs to be created

00:44:13.720 --> 00:44:15.380 align:middle line:90%
or already exists.

00:44:15.380 --> 00:44:17.430 align:middle line:84%
The more fundamentally
weighted indexes.

00:44:17.430 --> 00:44:20.950 align:middle line:90%
So what drives stock markets--

00:44:20.950 --> 00:44:22.330 align:middle line:84%
Stock market
indices today, if we

00:44:22.330 --> 00:44:25.160 align:middle line:84%
think about the Dow Jones
Industrial Average is a price

00:44:25.160 --> 00:44:25.960 align:middle line:90%
weighted index.

00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:28.600 align:middle line:10%
If we think about
NASDAQ and S&P,

00:44:28.600 --> 00:44:31.630 align:middle line:10%
they are market
weighted indices.

00:44:31.630 --> 00:44:36.320 align:middle line:84%
And both those indices would
be great if we already operate

00:44:36.320 --> 00:44:38.920 align:middle line:84%
at the mental level, but
the fact is, we don't.

00:44:38.920 --> 00:44:41.830 align:middle line:84%
And so at the vital
level, they just

00:44:41.830 --> 00:44:44.860 align:middle line:84%
magnify whatever the direction
that things are already

00:44:44.860 --> 00:44:46.060 align:middle line:90%
going on.

00:44:46.060 --> 00:44:47.240 align:middle line:90%
They already go there.

00:44:47.240 --> 00:44:49.480 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things
is that we would

00:44:49.480 --> 00:44:52.540 align:middle line:84%
need to put much more
weightage on fundamentally

00:44:52.540 --> 00:44:53.344 align:middle line:90%
weighted indices.

00:44:53.344 --> 00:44:54.760 align:middle line:84%
And fundamentally
weighted indices

00:44:54.760 --> 00:44:57.190 align:middle line:84%
means that we're getting
to the true value

00:44:57.190 --> 00:44:58.810 align:middle line:84%
that a company is
actually creating.

00:44:58.810 --> 00:45:01.270 align:middle line:90%
So what are it's true sales?

00:45:01.270 --> 00:45:02.380 align:middle line:90%
What are its true costs?

00:45:02.380 --> 00:45:04.970 align:middle line:90%
What are its earnings?

00:45:04.970 --> 00:45:06.550 align:middle line:90%
What is it actually doing?

00:45:06.550 --> 00:45:10.860 align:middle line:84%
And that information
is used to weight

00:45:10.860 --> 00:45:12.220 align:middle line:90%
a proportion in an index.

00:45:12.220 --> 00:45:15.490 align:middle line:84%
So it's much more
realistic, and it

00:45:15.490 --> 00:45:17.410 align:middle line:90%
begins to ground things more.

00:45:17.410 --> 00:45:21.430 align:middle line:84%
So it's not this huge bubble
that's being acted on,

00:45:21.430 --> 00:45:26.740 align:middle line:84%
but there's a ground reality
by which investors can

00:45:26.740 --> 00:45:29.920 align:middle line:90%
make more grounded decisions.

00:45:29.920 --> 00:45:33.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Is there somewhere
where this already exists?

00:45:33.100 --> 00:45:35.320 align:middle line:90%
Is being tried, or?

00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, I'm not exactly
sure if it's actually existing

00:45:40.540 --> 00:45:44.380 align:middle line:84%
in any of the stock markets
today, or if it's an index.

00:45:44.380 --> 00:45:49.370 align:middle line:10%
But in studies
that have been done

00:45:49.370 --> 00:45:53.770 align:middle line:10%
where you have fundamentally
weighted indexes versus, say,

00:45:53.770 --> 00:45:58.330 align:middle line:10%
price weighted or the
market weighted indices

00:45:58.330 --> 00:46:01.960 align:middle line:10%
over a period of 30 to
40 years, those studies

00:46:01.960 --> 00:46:05.860 align:middle line:10%
have indicated that the
fundamentally weighted index

00:46:05.860 --> 00:46:11.890 align:middle line:10%
would outperform existing
indexes that are primarily

00:46:11.890 --> 00:46:16.430 align:middle line:10%
used to filter funds
into the stock market.

00:46:16.430 --> 00:46:19.540 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know if it's
actually being used,

00:46:19.540 --> 00:46:21.970 align:middle line:84%
but studies indicate
that it would--

00:46:21.970 --> 00:46:25.870 align:middle line:84%
by looking at real
companies, there was--

00:46:25.870 --> 00:46:27.700 align:middle line:84%
I forget who did
the study, but it

00:46:27.700 --> 00:46:31.650 align:middle line:84%
indicates that it would
yield a higher return.

00:46:31.650 --> 00:46:32.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:46:32.450 --> 00:46:36.250 align:middle line:84%
Instead of this unstable stuff,
where it's flying one day

00:46:36.250 --> 00:46:38.770 align:middle line:90%
and crashing the next.

00:46:38.770 --> 00:46:41.020 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:46:41.020 --> 00:46:45.100 align:middle line:84%
So is what we're looking at
more or less along the line,

00:46:45.100 --> 00:46:46.720 align:middle line:84%
in just colloquial
terms, of what

00:46:46.720 --> 00:46:49.810 align:middle line:84%
would be called socially
responsible investing

00:46:49.810 --> 00:46:50.950 align:middle line:90%
in addition to that?

00:46:50.950 --> 00:46:55.450 align:middle line:84%
Is that an add-on to that, or
a part of this fundamentally?

00:46:55.450 --> 00:46:56.320 align:middle line:90%
>> It's an add-on.

00:46:56.320 --> 00:47:00.850 align:middle line:10%
So I think that that's a really
good point, because actually,

00:47:00.850 --> 00:47:05.260 align:middle line:10%
what the market has been going
the way that it has been going

00:47:05.260 --> 00:47:08.470 align:middle line:10%
for a few decades, and
especially since 1995

00:47:08.470 --> 00:47:12.880 align:middle line:10%
to now, where things have gotten
incredibly in the vital level.

00:47:12.880 --> 00:47:15.610 align:middle line:10%
And there's been
this natural reaction

00:47:15.610 --> 00:47:19.690 align:middle line:10%
from a number of
stakeholders around the world

00:47:19.690 --> 00:47:23.230 align:middle line:10%
to put sanity into the way
investments take place.

00:47:23.230 --> 00:47:27.080 align:middle line:84%
Socially responsible
investing has, of course,

00:47:27.080 --> 00:47:29.164 align:middle line:84%
been going on for
probably as long

00:47:29.164 --> 00:47:30.580 align:middle line:84%
as the institution
of business has

00:47:30.580 --> 00:47:33.820 align:middle line:84%
existed, from the
religiously minded who--

00:47:33.820 --> 00:47:35.170 align:middle line:90%
initially we have said, OK.

00:47:35.170 --> 00:47:37.600 align:middle line:84%
Keep away from sin
industries or industries

00:47:37.600 --> 00:47:39.920 align:middle line:84%
that harm your
health, and so on.

00:47:39.920 --> 00:47:42.940 align:middle line:84%
But that's become a much
bigger movement today.

00:47:42.940 --> 00:47:47.890 align:middle line:84%
So of the available investments
of $25 trillion or so

00:47:47.890 --> 00:47:53.200 align:middle line:84%
in the US, $3 trillion of that
is through socially responsible

00:47:53.200 --> 00:47:54.502 align:middle line:90%
investing.

00:47:54.502 --> 00:47:55.710 align:middle line:90%
So it's a growing percentage.

00:47:55.710 --> 00:47:56.004 align:middle line:90%
>> That's big.

00:47:56.004 --> 00:47:56.200 align:middle line:90%
That's growing.

00:47:56.200 --> 00:47:56.650 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:47:56.650 --> 00:47:57.460 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:47:57.460 --> 00:48:00.790 align:middle line:84%
>> And then in addition to
that, just following up on that,

00:48:00.790 --> 00:48:03.640 align:middle line:84%
that's from-- so perhaps when
we think about it from the shift

00:48:03.640 --> 00:48:05.440 align:middle line:90%
from the vital to the mental.

00:48:05.440 --> 00:48:07.690 align:middle line:84%
We can see that socially
responsible investing

00:48:07.690 --> 00:48:11.117 align:middle line:84%
is perhaps from those
stakeholders who are already

00:48:11.117 --> 00:48:11.950 align:middle line:90%
at the mental level.

00:48:11.950 --> 00:48:13.116 align:middle line:90%
>> At the mental level, yes.

00:48:13.116 --> 00:48:14.080 align:middle line:90%
That makes sense.

00:48:14.080 --> 00:48:16.330 align:middle line:84%
>> But then if we think about
other movements that are

00:48:16.330 --> 00:48:17.130 align:middle line:90%
occurring.

00:48:17.130 --> 00:48:21.620 align:middle line:10%
So have this whole--

00:48:21.620 --> 00:48:24.580 align:middle line:10%
the GRI, the Global
Reporting Initiative

00:48:24.580 --> 00:48:27.460 align:middle line:10%
that started, again,
in reaction to the way

00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:29.750 align:middle line:10%
that things have been
going the last 15 years

00:48:29.750 --> 00:48:36.440 align:middle line:10%
or so, where there's a lot
more parameters, factors that

00:48:36.440 --> 00:48:39.800 align:middle line:10%
have to do with the environment
and cost to society that

00:48:39.800 --> 00:48:42.740 align:middle line:10%
are also integrated
into evaluating

00:48:42.740 --> 00:48:45.290 align:middle line:10%
or how a company is doing.

00:48:45.290 --> 00:48:47.690 align:middle line:84%
So that becomes
a filter as well.

00:48:47.690 --> 00:48:49.450 align:middle line:84%
So you have that
movement, the GRI.

00:48:49.450 --> 00:48:51.500 align:middle line:84%
Then you have PRI,
which is the Principles

00:48:51.500 --> 00:48:55.910 align:middle line:84%
of Responsible Investing,
which is financial institutions

00:48:55.910 --> 00:48:59.560 align:middle line:84%
themselves looking at how
they can be more responsible

00:48:59.560 --> 00:49:03.770 align:middle line:84%
and factor in environmental,
social governance

00:49:03.770 --> 00:49:07.520 align:middle line:84%
considerations into who
they choose to invest with.

00:49:07.520 --> 00:49:09.100 align:middle line:84%
So a number of
different stakeholders

00:49:09.100 --> 00:49:13.220 align:middle line:84%
around the world who perhaps
we can say are more at that--

00:49:13.220 --> 00:49:16.080 align:middle line:84%
either at the mental level
or wanting to go there,

00:49:16.080 --> 00:49:20.630 align:middle line:84%
are putting into place
these different frameworks

00:49:20.630 --> 00:49:21.750 align:middle line:90%
from the outside.

00:49:21.750 --> 00:49:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And then the fact also is that
there's been this huge movement

00:49:25.200 --> 00:49:28.010 align:middle line:90%
from the bottom up.

00:49:28.010 --> 00:49:30.273 align:middle line:10%
Peter Hawkins, in his
book, "Blessed Unrest"--

00:49:30.273 --> 00:49:31.106 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, Paul Hawkins.

00:49:31.106 --> 00:49:31.230 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:49:31.230 --> 00:49:32.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:49:32.030 --> 00:49:33.080 align:middle line:90%
I mean Paul Hawkins.

00:49:33.080 --> 00:49:33.880 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:49:33.880 --> 00:49:38.720 align:middle line:84%
He reflects on how a million
to 2 million organizations

00:49:38.720 --> 00:49:42.830 align:middle line:84%
around the world
are actually trying

00:49:42.830 --> 00:49:45.770 align:middle line:84%
to combat a lot of the
environmental and social ills

00:49:45.770 --> 00:49:47.480 align:middle line:84%
that have been
created as a result

00:49:47.480 --> 00:49:50.930 align:middle line:84%
of our irresponsible
investing in business.

00:49:50.930 --> 00:49:53.060 align:middle line:84%
>> And to say nothing
of Occupy Wall Street.

00:49:53.060 --> 00:49:54.351 align:middle line:90%
>> Occupy Wall Street, exactly.

00:49:54.351 --> 00:49:57.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Just basically objecting
to the way money is used

00:49:57.230 --> 00:50:00.650 align:middle line:84%
and managed and
exploited and wasted.

00:50:00.650 --> 00:50:02.220 align:middle line:90%
Just that in itself.

00:50:02.220 --> 00:50:03.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes.

00:50:03.020 --> 00:50:03.820 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:50:03.820 --> 00:50:07.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that what's
being indicated just very

00:50:07.640 --> 00:50:11.870 align:middle line:84%
organically from the way that
business flow is interacting

00:50:11.870 --> 00:50:14.600 align:middle line:84%
with life is that there are
a number of stakeholders

00:50:14.600 --> 00:50:17.262 align:middle line:84%
from many different places
and perspectives who

00:50:17.262 --> 00:50:18.470 align:middle line:90%
are waking up and saying, no.

00:50:18.470 --> 00:50:19.428 align:middle line:90%
This isn't going to do.

00:50:19.428 --> 00:50:22.520 align:middle line:90%
And the question is how can we--

00:50:22.520 --> 00:50:24.830 align:middle line:84%
what I talk about in
the book is how can we

00:50:24.830 --> 00:50:28.160 align:middle line:84%
really go the next
step and integrate that

00:50:28.160 --> 00:50:30.770 align:middle line:84%
into the actual way that
the stock market functions.

00:50:30.770 --> 00:50:33.170 align:middle line:84%
So it's well and
good when you have

00:50:33.170 --> 00:50:36.080 align:middle line:84%
all these different filters
being applied from the outside,

00:50:36.080 --> 00:50:38.510 align:middle line:84%
and you have indices
that are set up

00:50:38.510 --> 00:50:42.086 align:middle line:84%
that may filter funds
into the stock market,

00:50:42.086 --> 00:50:43.460 align:middle line:84%
but the question
is can the stock

00:50:43.460 --> 00:50:48.110 align:middle line:84%
market itself be changed so
that these filters become part

00:50:48.110 --> 00:50:51.390 align:middle line:84%
of the heuristics that
automatically determine

00:50:51.390 --> 00:50:54.650 align:middle line:84%
the pricing of stocks
on a day-to-day basis.

00:50:54.650 --> 00:50:56.550 align:middle line:90%
>> What's the answer to that?

00:50:56.550 --> 00:50:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Currently, no.

00:50:57.350 --> 00:50:59.810 align:middle line:84%
I think absolutely possible
with the technology

00:50:59.810 --> 00:51:02.340 align:middle line:90%
that we have existing today.

00:51:02.340 --> 00:51:06.170 align:middle line:84%
So when we think about
what would it really take

00:51:06.170 --> 00:51:09.530 align:middle line:84%
to make something like that
work, just very practically

00:51:09.530 --> 00:51:11.960 align:middle line:84%
speaking, you would
need to have sensors

00:51:11.960 --> 00:51:15.080 align:middle line:84%
in the environment, nano
sensors that would pick up

00:51:15.080 --> 00:51:18.200 align:middle line:84%
if there was any
kind of compromise

00:51:18.200 --> 00:51:22.160 align:middle line:84%
to, say, the quality of
water or the quality of air

00:51:22.160 --> 00:51:24.120 align:middle line:90%
or the quality of the soil.

00:51:24.120 --> 00:51:27.840 align:middle line:84%
And if you had nano sensors
in these different places,

00:51:27.840 --> 00:51:29.060 align:middle line:90%
it would pick it up.

00:51:29.060 --> 00:51:32.990 align:middle line:84%
And then these could be part
of a network, a secure network,

00:51:32.990 --> 00:51:37.640 align:middle line:84%
that are fed back into stock
exchanges around the world.

00:51:37.640 --> 00:51:44.060 align:middle line:84%
And you would have filters
and the actual algorithms that

00:51:44.060 --> 00:51:47.720 align:middle line:84%
exist or that should exist in
the functioning of the stock

00:51:47.720 --> 00:51:50.450 align:middle line:84%
market, to take
into account some

00:51:50.450 --> 00:51:52.340 align:middle line:84%
of these different
real-time inputs

00:51:52.340 --> 00:51:58.040 align:middle line:84%
that are very, very
important in factoring

00:51:58.040 --> 00:51:59.430 align:middle line:90%
what a stock price should be.

00:51:59.430 --> 00:52:05.150 align:middle line:84%
So for example, if we know
for a fact that you have, say,

00:52:05.150 --> 00:52:11.640 align:middle line:84%
a corporation like when the oil
spill happened just last year--

00:52:11.640 --> 00:52:12.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:52:12.440 --> 00:52:12.980 align:middle line:90%
BP.

00:52:12.980 --> 00:52:13.780 align:middle line:90%
>> BP.

00:52:13.780 --> 00:52:16.070 align:middle line:90%
BP, yes.

00:52:16.070 --> 00:52:18.740 align:middle line:10%
You have sensors that
pick up that something's

00:52:18.740 --> 00:52:22.250 align:middle line:10%
totally awry over
there, and then you

00:52:22.250 --> 00:52:25.700 align:middle line:10%
know what the source of that is.

00:52:25.700 --> 00:52:28.760 align:middle line:84%
This would go and put an
automatic stop on trading

00:52:28.760 --> 00:52:34.820 align:middle line:84%
of BP and plus slow down the
whole category of oil and gas,

00:52:34.820 --> 00:52:38.486 align:middle line:84%
so every other company in
that, until it could be proven

00:52:38.486 --> 00:52:40.610 align:middle line:84%
